cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.SC 

The paper deals with the analysis of logic languages, specifically logic program analysis, using abstract interpretation. This falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) categories. The paper also discusses the problem of making abstract domains condensing, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper mentions the use of quantales, which are mathematical structures used in the study of semirings and formal languages, placing it under the category of symbolic computation (cs.SC).
